        Official Singles Chart on 15/1/2021

        15 January 2021 - 21 January 2021

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        So, my take on ‘Drivers License’…

        … oh, my, God, wow! I was kind of in the same boat as everyone else in the sense that I was confused how a debut single from someone who is only briefly known for acting in High School Musical: The Musical: The Series could already get millions of streams each day, but then I actually heard the song & it became very clear as to why.

        It has been months, maybe even years, since I heard a break-up anthem with this much raw emotion, which becomes even more incredible when you realise that Olivia Rodrigo is only 17 years old! It’s not just the singing either; the songwriting is immaculate too. It hits in such a potent yet bittersweet way, which is only highlighted further by that mesmerising bridge, which reminded me of Lorde’s voice when she was at her very best, occupied with the angelic production backing it up!

        It’s relatable, it’s powerful, every feature about this song comes from the core of the heart & while I’m not going to say this will be the biggest song of 2021 just yet (we’re only halfway into the first month of the year), I can safely say that Olivia Rodrigo has set the bar extremely high going forward, both in commercial success & critical reception.

        It’s an easy 10/10 for me! I genuinely wouldn’t mind this staying at #1 until ACR hits it. You know what, it could be there for even longer & honestly, it would deserve it! :D
